"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-ruth-chepngetich-chicago-marathon-world-record-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Kenyan Ruth Chepngetich ran the fastest women's marathon in history to win the Chicago Marathon on Sunday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 11, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Book_of_Ruth\", \"score\": 0.854446972869163, \"rank\": 0.17034762792816238, \"text\": \"Ruth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Book_of_Ruth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Book_of_Ruth\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chepngetich, 30, clocked 2 hours, 9 minutes, 56 seconds, crushing the world record of 2:11:53 set by Ethiopian Tigst Assefa at the 2023 Berlin Marathon.\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 209, \"end\": 218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.975426091745463, \"rank\": 0.025192995274141178, \"text\": \"Ethiopian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is my dream that has come true,\\\" Chepngetich said on NBC Chicago.\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 321, \"end\": 324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.8756740818013599, \"rank\": 0.12554062368254085, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 325, \"end\": 332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"score\": 0.9996420129429029, \"rank\": 0.0003514841008392369, \"text\": \"Chicago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I fight a lot thinking about world record.\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 377, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am fulfilled.\\\"\", \"from\": 378, \"to\": 394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chepngetich won the Chicago Marathon for the third time and distanced runner-up Sutume Kebede of Ethiopia by 7:36.\", \"from\": 396, \"to\": 510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 493, \"end\": 501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999999927699719, \"rank\": 7.221303381531888e-09, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chepngetich entered the race as the fourth-fastest woman in history with a personal best of 2:14:18.\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 611, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CHICAGO MARATHON:Results  Chepngetich not only became the first woman to break 2:10, but also the first woman to average sub-five-minute miles for a marathon (4:57), which means she's also the first woman to run faster than 12 miles per hour for a marathon.\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 870, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Four of the five fastest women's marathons in history have been run on the pancake-flat Chicago course over the last six years.\", \"from\": 872, \"to\": 999, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 960, \"end\": 967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"score\": 0.9996420129429029, \"rank\": 0.0003514841008392369, \"text\": \"Chicago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chicago\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before the 2019 Chicago Marathon, the women's marathon world record was 2:15:25.\", \"from\": 1000, \"to\": 1080, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chepngetich was ninth in her most recent marathon in London in April after an injury in February curtailed her build-up.\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1135, \"end\": 1141, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.99997537536